[SN]TITLE[SN]
AC Milan 3-2 Torino

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Striker Carlos Bacca scored a hat-trick as AC Milan opened their Serie A season with a dramatic win over Torino.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 29-year-old, who was linked with a move to West Ham in the summer, gave the hosts the lead before the break only for Andrea Belotti to equalise.
Bacca scored with a low strike and completed his treble with a penalty.
Daniele Baselli's late goal made it 3-2 before home keeper Gianluigi Donnarumma saved Belotti's injury-time penalty after Gabriel Paletta was sent off.
